<sn><md>### Course Learning Outcomes (CLOs)

Upon completion, students will be able to:

* **CLO 1:** Understand processes and endpoints in the human body related to toxic agent exposure.
* **CLO 2:** Demonstrate knowledge of risk assessment and management for environmental toxic agents.
* **CLO 3:** Master major issues and concepts in environmental toxicology.
* **CLO 4:** Source and synthesize information regarding environmental toxicology and chemistry.
* **CLO 5:** Analyze the occurrence and significance of major environmental toxicants for public health and sustainability.

</md></sn><sn><md>### Course Contents

| Topic                                        | Details                                                                                                                                              |
| -------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Introduction to Environmental Toxicology** | Principles<br>classification of toxic substances<br>abiotic transformation<br>environmental transport<br>xenobiotics<br>environmental thermodynamics |
| **Environmental Toxicants**                  | Sources and exposure pathways<br>biotransformation and metabolism<br>heavy metals, pesticides, PCBs, dioxins<br>air pollutants                       |
| **Fate of Toxicants**                        | Monitoring techniques<br>bioaccumulation<br>biomagnification<br>transfer between environmental spheres                                               |
| **Environmental Changes and Health**         | Environmental diseases<br>cancer<br>birth defects<br>respiratory diseases caused by pollutants                                                       |
| **Mutagenic and Carcinogenic Pollutants**    | Mutation types and effects<br>environmental cancer development stages<br>carcinogen metabolism                                                       |
| **Action Mechanisms**                        | Toxic effects on plants and mammals<br>endocrine disruption<br>xenobiotic action factors                                                             |
| **Case Studies**                             | Arsenic ecotoxicology<br>selenium toxicity<br>agrochemical, industrial, and transport-related toxicities                                             |

</md></sn><sn><md>### Recommended Readings

* *Advance in Environmental Science and Technology, Vol. 3: Environmental Biochemistry* — Rajvaidya and Markandey
* *Fundamentals of Environmental Chemistry* — Stanley E. Manahan
* *Environmental Toxicology: Impacts of Environmental Toxicants on Living Systems* — Yu</md></sn>